[{"question":"Is it a lawsuit?","answer":"It\u0027s actually a subpoena.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":23,"aSentId":24},{"question":"When was it?","answer":"Just like this -- never.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":39,"aSentId":40},{"question":"Really?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":41,"aSentId":42},{"question":"Why are you doing this?","answer":"Well, you invited me and I\u0027m intrigued by you, and I\u0027m someone who watches your show almost every night, and I\u0027m just intrigued and also, of course, it\u0027s an opportunity to talk about empowering women, empowering minorities and the fact that we still have not won complete equality in this country.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":43,"aSentId":44},{"question":"Which Gloria Allred are you?","answer":"Well, I\u0027m the Gloria Allred who is an attorney at part of our law firm of Allred, Marco and Goldberg.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":59,"aSentId":60},{"question":"Do you believe that men and women should be absolutely equal in everything?","answer":"I do believe that, under the law, under the Constitution of the United States, and under our public policy, that women deserve and should have a right to enjoy equal employment opportunity.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":68,"aSentId":69},{"question":"Do you ever do anything for publicity?","answer":"We do cases of public interest and importance.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":79,"aSentId":80},{"question":"Or should there be equality because simply because a woman may not have the power of a man to play to that ability?","answer":"It really depends on the particular facts.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":90,"aSentId":91},{"question":"Do you feel as aggrieved for men who get treated badly by women bosses?","answer":"Well, we have --","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":106,"aSentId":107},{"question":"Or is it all women against men?","answer":"Well, we actually have had a number of cases, where we represent men who have been discriminated against in employment, on account of their gender.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":109,"aSentId":110},{"question":"Does that worry you?","answer":"No, not at all, because we are a plaintiff\u0027s law firm.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":115,"aSentId":116},{"question":"Do you like that status?","answer":"Well, I like empowering my clients.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":145,"aSentId":146},{"question":"Why did you feel compelled to expose him?","answer":"Well, it matters if any man hurts any woman.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":160,"aSentId":161},{"question":"She was a porn, right?","answer":"They had -- she had -- she was an adult film star, yes.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":167,"aSentId":168},{"question":"And I just wonder sometimes, when you watch what she did afterwards, do you slightly sit back and go, maybe I should have left that one alone?","answer":"Not at all.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":191,"aSentId":192},{"question":"Really?","answer":"No.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":193,"aSentId":194},{"question":"Do you ever regret afterwards taking on cases, because of the way that perhaps the person you\u0027ve been defending or prosecuting on behalf of, because of their behavior afterwards, you have moments of self-reflection afterwards?","answer":"No, I\u0027m so proud of my clients and the courage they\u0027ve shown.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":202,"aSentId":203},{"question":"Does she -- does she not care about Ms. Woods?","answer":"Of course, she did.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":221,"aSentId":222},{"question":"But do you care about women being hurt by men whom they trusted, whom they loved, who they had every reason to believe loved them?","answer":"I get that.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":223,"aSentId":224},{"question":"Ever?","answer":"They have to survive.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":247,"aSentId":248},{"question":"Or is it always strictly legal?","answer":"Well, we represent victims\u0027 rights.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":265,"aSentId":266},{"question":"Should having an affair preclude a man from running for office?","answer":"I think that if --","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":274,"aSentId":275},{"question":"So, where do you draw the line?","answer":"Well, I think that politicians, if they are going to seek the highest office in our land, the presidency of the United States of America, they need to be honest with the American public, and just put it all out there, and not be hypocrites, not present themselves as the perfect family man.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":278,"aSentId":279},{"question":"Are you happy for him to restart politically, if you like?","answer":"Well, let me just say -- I mean, I\u0027m not a person who\u0027s going to vote for any of the potential Republican nominees for the presidency of the United States.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":287,"aSentId":288},{"question":"What happened to that guy that raped you?","answer":"I have no idea.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":331,"aSentId":332},{"question":"Did you ever see or hear of him again?","answer":"I never did.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":333,"aSentId":334},{"question":"You never found out what happened to him?","answer":"Never found out.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":341,"aSentId":342},{"question":"What are your feelings towards him now?","answer":"LLRED: You know, I generally don\u0027t look back.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":343,"aSentId":344},{"question":"Were you able to forgive your first husband for the abuse when you discovered about this bipolar?","answer":"You know, it wasn\u0027t about forgiving.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":360,"aSentId":361},{"question":"How great is my mom?","answer":"She\u0027s pretty special, your mother.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":381,"aSentId":382},{"question":"She\u0027s given it to you, hasn\u0027t she?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":388,"aSentId":389},{"question":"Does she?","answer":"I\u0027ll answer, too.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":402,"aSentId":403},{"question":"Is that true?","answer":"And no one can remember when I took a vacation --","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":425,"aSentId":426},{"question":"You never have a vacation?","answer":"I\u0027ve had a vacation -- well, years ago, I took my grandchildren on vacations --","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":427,"aSentId":428},{"question":"ORGAN: Why?","answer":"Because I have too much to do to fight injustice that still exists for my clients, for women and minorities.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":431,"aSentId":432},{"question":"You have a 10-year-old car, is that true?","answer":"I do.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":434,"aSentId":435},{"question":"But then -- but then I come back to the Tiger Woods case that you heard us debating earlier where I kind of think, why would this women, who does all this incredible stuff, take on a porn star to basically flim/flam Tiger Woods, really?","answer":"Can I -- let me respond to that, Piers, because --","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":463,"aSentId":464},{"question":"What do you think?","answer":"I\u0027ll tell you what I think.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":465,"aSentId":466},{"question":"Or the age discrimination case that we won?","answer":"Most of what she does.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":498,"aSentId":499},{"question":"Were you as proud?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":510,"aSentId":511},{"question":"May I finish, please?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":524,"aSentId":525},{"question":"Then why are you saying \"porn star,\" as if that\u0027s relevant?","answer":"I\u0027m just wondering whether, when your mother takes on a case like that, which is obviously so high-profile, obviously going to get so much attention, when you see this victim as she\u0027s being portrayed, go on to make another movie --","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":535,"aSentId":536},{"question":"Well, so what?","answer":"-- in which she uses Tiger Woods --","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":537,"aSentId":538},{"question":"And exploit it and commercialize it?","answer":"And she\u0027s a victim.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":548,"aSentId":549},{"question":"And why don\u0027t you spend as much talking about the fact that Tiger Woods should apologize to the women that he hurt?","answer":"He did apologize.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":550,"aSentId":551},{"question":"Well, do you like having this famous, infamous mother?","answer":"I love my mother.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":576,"aSentId":577},{"question":"Does she get mischaracterized, do you think?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":584,"aSentId":585},{"question":"How much of that is her own fault for taking on cases which are inflammatory?","answer":"None.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":586,"aSentId":587},{"question":"Why does your mother take on celebrity cases?","answer":"Listen, we\u0027re talking about the media.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":598,"aSentId":599},{"question":"Can you not persuade your mother to drop all the scandalous celebrity cases?","answer":"Because I don\u0027t consider them to be scandalous celebrity cases.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":603,"aSentId":604},{"question":"Is that right?","answer":"They\u0027re not scandalous celebrity cases.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":608,"aSentId":609},{"question":"Why?","answer":"LOOM: The media -- because I care about them and they have viable -- they\u0027re human beings, Piers.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":613,"aSentId":614},{"question":"How many times have you been properly in love, Gloria?","answer":"OK.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":632,"aSentId":633},{"question":"ORGAN: Is it a lawsuit?","answer":"It\u0027s actually a subpoena.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":635,"aSentId":636},{"question":"Would you like to fall in love again?","answer":"No.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":664,"aSentId":665},{"question":"Really?","answer":"No, I don\u0027t have time, and I don\u0027t want to make that investment.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":666,"aSentId":667},{"question":"Really?","answer":"Much younger men.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":685,"aSentId":686},{"question":"Really?","answer":"We have a saying in the women\u0027s movement, become the person you wanted to marry.","docId":"120323pmt","qSentId":687,"aSentId":688}]